message.content:
We start by extracting the key numbers from the reporting dates (all “End_amount” values):

1. Total Current Assets = 9,193,203.41  
   Total Current Liabilities = 728,279.50

2. From the income statement:  
   Gross Profit = 2,545,589.48  
   Total Revenue = 5,565,589.48  
   Net Profit = 1,095,371.35

3. From the balance sheet:  
   Total Assets = 14,823,650.85  
   (No additional non‐current liabilities are provided so we assume Total Liabilities = Total Current Liabilities.)

4. Cash & Cash Equivalents ending balance from the cash flow (which is the sum of “Cash on Hand” and “Bank Deposits”) = 7,242,255.76

5. From the cash flow statement:  
   Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –81,548.37  
   Purchase of Fixed Assets (Capital Expenditure) = 676,195.87  
   (Free Cash Flow (FCF) is calculated as Operating Cash Flow minus CapEx.)

Now we calculate each metric step by step:

A. Current Ratio  
  = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
  = 9,193,203.41 / 728,279.50  
  ≈ 12.62

B. Gross Profit Margin  
  = (Gross Profit / Revenue) × 100%  
  = (2,545,589.48 / 5,565,589.48) × 100%  
  ≈ 45.78%

C. Debt to Asset Ratio  
  = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 728,279.50 / 14,823,650.85  
  ≈ 0.05

D. Net Profit Margin  
  = (Net Profit / Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1,095,371.35 / 5,565,589.48) × 100%  
  ≈ 19.69%

E. Cash to Current Debt Ratio  
  = Cash and Cash Equivalents / Total Current Liabilities  
  = 7,242,255.76 / 728,279.50  
  ≈ 9.95

F. Free Cash Flow (FCF)  
  = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities – Capital Expenditures  
  = (–81,548.37) – 676,195.87  
  ≈ –757,744.24

G. Return on Assets (ROA)  
  = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (1,095,371.35 / 14,823,650.85) × 100%  
  ≈ 7.39%

Thus, the solution is:

    "Current Ratio": "12.62",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.78%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.05",
    "Net Profit Margin": "19.69%",
    "Cash to Current Debt Ratio": "9.95",
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-757744.24",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "7.39%"
  }
}
